# Development Workflow & Tooling

## Development Commands
- `pnpm dev` - Start development server with Turbopack
- `pnpm build` - Build for production
- `pnpm start` - Start production server
- `pnpm lint` - Run ESLint

## Code Quality Tools
- **ESLint**: Configured with Next.js rules in [eslint.config.mjs](mdc:eslint.config.mjs)
- **Prettier**: Auto-formatting with Tailwind plugin in [prettier.config.js](mdc:prettier.config.js)
- **TypeScript**: Strict mode enabled for type safety

## shadcn/ui Integration
- Configuration in [components.json](mdc:components.json)
- Use `npx shadcn@latest add <component>` to add new UI components
- Components are installed to [components/ui/](mdc:components/ui/)
- Aliases configured for easy imports: `@/components`, `@/lib`, `@/hooks`

## Theme System
- Theme provider in [components/theme-provider.tsx](mdc:components/theme-provider.tsx)
- CSS variables defined in [app/globals.css](mdc:app/globals.css)
- Dark/light mode switching with system preference detection
- Theme colors follow shadcn/ui neutral base color scheme

## Asset Management
- Static assets in [public/](mdc:public/) directory
- Project images organized in [public/img/projects/](mdc:public/img/projects/)
- Favicon and other meta assets in [app/](mdc:app/) directory

## Performance Considerations
- Next.js 15 with Turbopack for fast development
- Font optimization with `next/font/google`
- CSS variables for efficient theming
- Tree-shaking enabled for optimal bundle size

## MDX Support
- MDX components configured in [mdx-components.tsx](mdc:mdx-components.tsx)
- Remark GFM plugin for GitHub Flavored Markdown
- Custom styling for MDX content
